      <akn:section eId="sec_4_603">
        <akn:num>4-603</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Set-off.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-603_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, whenever the District is a defendant in a proceeding brought by a beneficiary, it shall have a right to set off from a judgment against it any damages that represent compensation for the care and treatment it has undertaken to provide or pay for as health-care assistance.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_4-603_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>No set-off shall be allowed from a judgment entered against the District pursuant to any provision of Chapter 13 of Title 7.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
